This paper deals with the use of computational techniques to analyze large corpora of documents associated with social phenomena. The paper discusses the use of semantic features in addition to keyword-based techniques, which suggests a focus on natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses information retrieval techniques, which suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of visualization techniques to gain insights into the underlying phenomenon suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and computer graphics (cs.CY).
